review_blob: An underappreciated American lager. Light malty aroma with a pleasant aftertaste. Id take this any day over a Miller or a Bud.
Beautiful color, smooth lingering maltiness and lots of hops. Cant wait for next spring!
A good, but not great amber. A litte bit watery, but has a really nice crisp hop finish.

This is an amazing dry stout. Creamy smooth roasted grain flavor with a nice hoppy dry finish. At the risk of being called a heretic, I might choose it over Guinness Stout if both were available on draught.
A real disappointment. Quite an ordinary light ale.
This beer has it all. Rich malty flavor, a little sweet, and quite hoppy. Dont drink it ice cold or you will be disappointed.
This is the benchmark for American pale ales.
This is a sensuous beer. From watching it settle in the glass to taking the first creamy, velvety sip it is pure heaven.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Light amber color, good malt flavor and a nice lingering hoppy finish.  Perhaps the perfect picnic beer....mingles perfectly with brats and potato salad.
Distinct barley flavor and quite dry. Great ice cold with some chili or spicey goulash.

That this beer sells so well is evidence (if further evidence were needed) that Americans are sheep. I just had my first bottle in probably ten years. This beer is slightly sweet and utterly without character.

FWIW, Im not a big brown ale fan, but I really like this beer. It is rich and smooth with a lasting nutty flavor. 
Slightly off topic, but the Goose Island brewpub in Chicago has what may be the best homemade potato chips on the planet.

I had a bottle of this recently for the first time since I was in college. I shake my head in wonder at how I could have drank so much of this stuff when I was younger. It starts out nice enough with a rich nutty flavor, but then falls flat on its face. No character and an aftertaste worthy of a warm, year-old can of Old Style.

A new Belgian white from Lakefront. This is the best US-brewed white Ive had since the late, lamented Celis turned off their brew kettles for good. Rich maltiness with a hint of cardamom and citrus....not overwhelming, just right.
Too fruity and sweet. This stuff tastes unnatural. Of course it is made by Coors, so what can be expected.

I really like this beer. When it is fresh (check those dates!) it is citrusy, spicey and refreshing. Sadly, Sprecher stopped making their other two wheat beers, Milwaukee Weiss and a Dunkel Weizen that was out of this world. They were both better than the Hefe.  A moment of silence for those late great wheats....

This is not a great beer by any means, but it IS a great beer on a really hot day. It has a light maltiness and a very dry finish. Buy it only from a liquor store which sells a lot of it. Skunks easily....damn green bottles.
It smells faintly of bannanas, but dont let that put you off.  This is a rich, malty and somewhat spicey beer which is great with lighter food.

This is a great american pale ale. Nice flowery, hoppy nose and a clean finish.  The earlier reviewer is absolutely correct about the freshness of this stuff and all Lakefront beers. They arent pasteurized and age poorly.
A glorious amber with a rich malty taste, mild hoppiness and a rich, almost creamy finish.
